Paris Dylan

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

A commission of @findingavarice521.

Paris Dylan is an American model and social media personality, known for appearing in some reality TV shows and for being the girlfriend of famous songwriter Don McLean (of American Pie fame).

4200-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with 1 batch size and gradient acc. steps. While on holidays, I'll use this setup when I train TIs on my brother's PC (@zepekenh0, check out his debut TI cause I think it's pretty good ^^). I'll also keep using @Scottymac's free online colab to experiment with different settings every now and then.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my (usual) work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (p4r1sdy:0.99), a woman as a movie star, hair upsweep updo, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

Madison Kate

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Madison Kate is an American cosplayer and model on Instagram.

This is a 1500-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images using JernauGurgeh's method of training embeddings. It seems to work best with Avalon, Cyberrealistic, and Lyriel models. Feel free to experiment!

How to create a good prompt using this TI

JernauGurgeh recommends starting with this phrase specifically

"photo of m4dikat, a woman"
